        <item>
            <title>Version 1.0.1</title>
            <pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>2</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.0.1</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[
                <ul>
                    <li>Fixed privileged helper detection: the app could report the helper as "not installed" or stuck requiring approval even when it was actually enabled, because status was read from a long-lived cached handle instead of a fresh system query</li>
                </ul>
            ]]></description>
            <enclosure
                url="https://github.com/FMDigitech/WireTunnels/releases/download/v1.0.1/WireTunnels-1.0.1.zip"
                sparkle:edSignature="qEstLRqa5bv7T964Mq8w6PKwbqDNXSMm8ib6cZvio5CNPxetjijf0nNDnLw/LeUW9SU6TRRaTBbuP/DC2NGsDQ=="
                length="10788342"
                type="application/octet-stream"
            />
        </item>

        <item>
            <title>Version 1.0.2</title>
            <pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>3</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.0.2</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[
                <ul>
                    <li>Shared tunnels: administrators can create tunnels visible to every user on the Mac, control who's allowed to connect or disconnect, and see who's currently connected</li>
                    <li>On-Demand rules can now connect and disconnect on different Wi-Fi networks independently, instead of a single action per tunnel</li>
                    <li>Pick Wi-Fi networks for On-Demand rules from a list of known networks, or type one manually</li>
                    <li>Shared tunnel changes now ask for your admin password once per session instead of every time</li>
                    <li>Added a "Hide Dock Icon" option in Settings for menu-bar-only use</li>
                    <li>Fixed On-Demand rules for specific Wi-Fi networks not triggering (this needed Location permission to read the current network name)</li>
                </ul>
            ]]></description>
            <enclosure
                url="https://github.com/FMDigitech/WireTunnels/releases/download/v1.0.2/WireTunnels-1.0.2.zip"
                sparkle:edSignature="KFMha65u3pX2fvov9mdngyK/R+FzKwSfJAo0QLTu0FYXRRYAxyqUJwVjwfXcYxDN4spHRfujRyxXITLihvzIBw=="
                length="10801415"
                type="application/octet-stream"
            />
        </item>

